entries.meaning: (Sussex) A visit by one bonfire society to join in with the celebrations of another.
examples: Are you going to any outfires this year? Yes, Barcombe and Glynde I think.

verbs.description: outfire (third-person singular simple present outfires, present participle outfiring, simple past and past participle outfired)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To fire farther or better than.
examples: Outfiring the newest Nazi weapon four to one, an automatic, pneumatic gun developed by a Los Angeles inventor pours out 12,000 rounds a minute...
